eichen Bibliothek – vielleicht der des Origenes und Eusebius in Caesarea Maritima – konnten auch solche Werke exzerpiert werden, die später verloren gingen. Auch ohne die genaue Quellenanalyse der Edition gibt die Übersetzung ein umfassendes Bild dessen, was zu dieser Zeit als die gültige Exegese des Buches Genesis galt.  aThe Genesis Commentary by Procopius of Gaza (465/470–526/530) is the first part of his major commentary on most of the historical books of the Old Testament (CPG 7430). For the first time, it is presented along with a translation into a modern language and annotated notes, supplementing the recently published critical edition (GCS NF 22).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBibelkommentar. 4aKirchenvater. 4aProkop von Gaza. 4aSpätantike. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aPatristic Studies.  aProcopius of Gaza.  alate antique commentary.1 aMetzler, Karin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104356100 cprintz978311044276240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311043745440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110437454423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110437454/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGA